Installation:

1. Install prerequisites: sudo yum install redis munin-node
2. Configure redis to start at boot: sudo chkconfig redis on
3. Start redis: sudo service redis start
4. Install package: sudo ./INSTALL.sh
   This will also configure the munin plugins to record just the cpu, memory, network,
   and filesystem usage. For more information on configuring plugins, see the munin-node
   documentation.
5. Configure munin-node-reporter: edit "/usr/local/etc/munin-node-reporter.conf" and set
   "CollectorURL" tag to point to your collector.
6. Get cron to run munin-node-redis and munin-node-reporter: sudo service crond restart
7. Is it running? Wait five minutes and try: redis-cli keys '*' - is should give:
